author: Associated Press
title: NFL inactives: Seattle's Wagner out at Carolina; Lynch in
text:
Seattle All-Pro middle linebacker Bobby Wagner was out against Carolina because of a chest injury, but the Seahawks did have running back Marshawn Lynch active after he missed two games with a bad hamstring.
As expected, pass rusher Jared Allen was inactive for the Panthers on Sunday.
Wagner's absence, combined with injuries to Brock Coyle and Nick Moody, left Seattle thin at linebacker. The Seahawks had only four healthy linebackers, with Mike Morgan the only backup. Seattle planned to slide K.J. Wright over to fill in for Wagner and Kevin Pierre-Louis was expected to step into Wright's spot on the outside.
At Green Bay, the Chargers' battered offensive line was without guard Orlando Franklin (ankle). Fellow starters King Dunlap (concussion) and Chris Watt (groin/concussion) were declared out Friday.
The Packers' defense was without tackle B.J. Raji (groin) and linebacker Nick Perry (shoulder/hand), both hurt in last week's win over St. Louis.
Wide receiver Steve Smith, who missed time with a back injury, was active for Baltimore's game at San Francisco.
